{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3138033,"name":"","username":"Kirby285","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/4af34b/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-02-01T23:57:00.828Z","cooked":"<p>Hey, I am on team 1555 and we were trying to get limit switches ready for our robot and we kept on getting an error where the switch isn’t being resolved even if we have it initialized further up in the code.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.DigitalInput;

  @Override
  public void robotInit() {

    DigitalInput m_switch = new DigitalInput(0);
}

  @Override
  public void teleopPeriodic() {

  if(m_switch.get()){
  System.out.println("Working?");  }
}
</code></pre>
