<p>If you move your variable declaration to outside of robotInit, then it will be accessable to the whole class.</p>
<p>Heres a quick example of what you could do:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-java">
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.DigitalInput;

  DigitalInput m_switch; 

  @Override
  public void robotInit() {

   m_switch = new DigitalInput(0);

}

  @Override
  public void teleopPeriodic() {

  if(m_switch.get()){
  System.out.println("Working?");  }
}

</code></pre>
